The functions of the Board shall be—
(a) to make recommendations to the Minister with respect to the exercise by him of his powers under section three;
to make recommendations to the Minister with respect to the exercise by him of his powers under section three;
(b) to exercise any power delegated to it under section four;
to exercise any power delegated to it under section four;
(c) to make investigations and surveys for the purpose of obtaining information and statistics of use to the Board in the exercise of any of its functions;
to make investigations and surveys for the purpose of obtaining information and statistics of use to the Board in the exercise of any of its functions;
(d) to furnish information and advice in relation to the decimal currency system, and to publish such information and other material, whether by advertisement or otherwise, as in its opinion is necessary or desirable for the purpose of facilitating the transition from the existing currency system to the decimal currency system;
